public interface Model
extends java.io.Serializable

Model interface to be implemented by the uptaker. The implementation class should have a default constructor so that VIN can use reflection to instantiate such object.

getEntity

Entity getEntity(EntityIdentifier entIdentifier)
                 throws VINException
Given an entity type and id, model should be able to retrieve this entity.

Parameters:
entIdentifier - Entity Identifier, it is passed to VIN bounded taskflow as a parameter from uptaker.
Returns:
The corresponding entity. Return null if such entity doesn't exist. NOTE: assume a pair of entity type and object id can be uniquely identity any entity. If not, we may change the two parameters to an EntityIdentity class to accommodate more identification related parameter(s).
Throws:
VINException
